1
00:00:00,145 --> 00:00:01,760
I'm talking to you about the dawn prayer

2
00:00:02,247 --> 00:00:03,939
You must wake up before the prayer

3
00:00:05,066 --> 00:00:07,770
And since you're inside, you need to be mindful of those behind you

4
00:00:08,670 --> 00:00:09,700
So they won't be held accountable

5
00:00:10,147 --> 00:00:13,155
Meaning you relieve yourself quickly, just for the prayer

6
00:00:14,648 --> 00:00:16,142
And you go for <i>wudu</i> [ablution]

7
00:00:16,910 --> 00:00:21,911
At normal times, when you enter the toilet

8
00:00:22,759 --> 00:00:25,107
You knock for the jailer, to go to the toilet

9
00:00:25,162 --> 00:00:27,204
He opens the door so you can go into the toilet

10
00:00:27,558 --> 00:00:31,321
Interviewer: Was the jailer cooperative, making it easy to get into the toilet?

11
00:00:31,431 --> 00:00:34,397
Yes, he says, Where to? You say, To the toilet, and he says, Go out

12
00:00:34,724 --> 00:00:38,460
Interviewer: Did he clash with you sometimes?
Witness: No, no

13
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:39,507
Interviewer: With anyone?

14
00:00:39,567 --> 00:00:43,959
Not with anyone, and we had nothing to do

15
00:00:44,712 --> 00:00:46,507
Interviewer: In this place was there just one jailer?

16
00:00:47,407 --> 00:00:49,087
There was one here in the corridor

17
00:00:49,482 --> 00:00:50,696
But over here I wasn't paying attention to him

18
00:00:50,721 --> 00:00:53,343
As you know, when he lets you out, he stands here

19
00:00:54,572 --> 00:00:56,088
You go straight in

20
00:00:56,342 --> 00:00:59,620
Interviewer: You were more than twenty people with one jailer?

21
00:00:59,726 --> 00:01:02,353
While using the toilet, did

22
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:05,292
two or three go out to relieve
themselves together, or did each person go alone?

23
00:01:05,338 --> 00:01:06,608
No, no, they go out one by one

24
00:01:07,322 --> 00:01:08,492
And when you go out, he closes the door behind you

25
00:01:08,682 --> 00:01:12,369
Interviewer: Didn’t you think, while you were in the prison, when the door opened

26
00:01:12,903 --> 00:01:19,852
And since he was one person alone, to try to escape?

27
00:01:20,175 --> 00:01:23,555
To overpower him or hit him? Didn't something like that ever happen?

28
00:01:23,620 --> 00:01:25,853
That idea exists, but you can’t do anything

29
00:01:26,033 --> 00:01:27,569
You assume there is just one person here

30
00:01:28,323 --> 00:01:30,782
But inside or on the rooftops you don’t know how many they are

31
00:01:30,907 --> 00:01:31,949
And they are armed

32
00:01:32,693 --> 00:01:36,728
The simplest thing is that he kills you without batting an eye

33
00:01:37,779 --> 00:01:41,120
Interviewer: Did you relieve yourself comfortably with no pressure?

34
00:01:41,288 --> 00:01:43,174
No, no, you go in and come out

35
00:01:43,668 --> 00:01:46,804
Only at prayer times, you have to hurry

36
00:01:47,445 --> 00:01:49,312
So those behind you won’t be held accountable

37
00:01:49,467 --> 00:01:51,634
Interviewer: You hurried out by choice? Witness: Yes, yes

38
00:01:51,863 --> 00:01:54,606
Interviewer: Did the prayer have a set time?

39
00:01:54,706 --> 00:01:57,539
Did you have to pray when the call to prayer started?

40
00:01:57,746 --> 00:02:02,442
A certain number of minutes from the call to prayer, or immediately after it finishes?

41
00:02:02,896 --> 00:02:05,383
When the call to prayer begins

42
00:02:06,577 --> 00:02:07,600
You perform <i>wudu</i> and finish the ablution

43
00:02:07,834 --> 00:02:10,650
He waits ten minutes or five minutes and starts the prayer

44
00:02:10,696 --> 00:02:12,735
Everyone must be in the hall for the prayer
